    {
      "id": "advanced-primitives-intro",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Overview",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -380,
        "y": -220
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-advanced-primitives"
        },
        "markdown": "# Advanced Primitives\n\nThese are real primitives, but not the normal starting point.\n\nAdvanced primitives here:\n- `bridge`\n- `script`\n- `field`\n\nUse them when a graph needs boundary authority, executable behavior, or explicit authored graph data."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "advanced-primitives-reader",
      "type": "view",
      "label": "Advanced Reader View",
      "position": {
        "x": 180,
        "y": -240
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-advanced-primitives"
        },
        "view": {
          "intent": "node",
          "payload": "node.web.detail"
        },
        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# Advanced Reader View\n\nThis node is the declared reading surface for the advanced primitives tutorial.\n\nAdvanced primitives still rely on the same surface rule as basic ones:\n- create the view node\n- expose it in the declaration\n- bind the declaration surface to the view node id\n\n`bridge`, `script`, and `field` may be more advanced, but they still show up through ordinary declared graph surfaces."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "advanced-primitives-bridge-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Bridge",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -380,
        "y": 100
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-advanced-primitives"
        },
        "markdown": "## Bridge\n\nUse `bridge` when authority crosses a boundary.\n\nA bridge can:\n- import node classes\n- expose or constrain resources\n- make a remote graph consumable in a controlled way"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "advanced-primitives-bridge-example",
      "type": "bridge",
      "label": "Example Bridge",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 80,
        "y": 120
      },
      "width": 320,
      "height": 180,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-advanced-primitives"
        },
        "memo": "Example bridge to the field node class.",
        "target": {
          "endpoint": "/library/classes/nodes/data-schema/field.node-class.node:root",
          "mode": "bridge",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "label": "Field",
          "key": "field"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "advanced-primitives-script-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Script",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -380,
        "y": 420
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-advanced-primitives"
        },
        "markdown": "## Script\n\nUse `script` for graph-visible executable behavior.\n\nA script should remain owned by a node.\nThe editor may be fancy, but the capability should still exist as a visible part of the graph."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "advanced-primitives-field-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Field",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -380,
        "y": 760
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-advanced-primitives"
        },
        "markdown": "## Field\n\nUse `field` for authored functional data.\n\nA field owns:\n- a `key`\n- a `fieldType`\n- a `value`\n- required/description metadata\n\nFields are how graphs carry real data without smearing that data into declaration or presentation."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "advanced-primitives-script-example",
      "type": "script",
      "label": "Example Script",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 80,
        "y": 420
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-advanced-primitives"
        },
        "scriptName": "Count Nodes",
        "dryRun": true,
        "allowMutations": false,
        "autoRun": false,
        "autoRunOnGraphChange": false,
        "summaryNodeId": "",
        "source": "const nodes = await api.getNodes();\nreturn { nodeCount: nodes.length, graphId: api.getGraphId?.() || null };"
      }
    },
